Rickettsiae:
Rickettsiae are  classified as "between" viruses and bacteria,
they are named after Dr.H. T. Ricketts who first isolated them,
Examples of Ricettsiae include : Rocky Rocky Mountain Spotted Fever, and Typhas Fever.
Rickettsiae are usally only transmitted by the bite of a tick, lice ,or flea.
Rickettsiae are combated with a normal coarse of antibiotics and vacines.